#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:1
msgid "For Hardware"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:3
msgid ""
"_Is the low-level / arch-specific code correct against the hardware and ABI "
"contract?_"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:5
msgid ""
"This is the index of the **hardware** guidelines. Each subsection is its own "
"page, and each entry below links a stable `short-name` to its guideline, "
"with a one-line gist so a reader (or a review tool) can grasp the guideline "
"before opening it."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:10
msgid "Index"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:12
msgid "**[Assembly Conventions](assembly-conventions.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:13
msgid ""
"[`asm-section-directives`](assembly-conventions.md#asm-section-directives): "
"Short directive for built-in sections; `.section` with flags for custom; "
"blank line after."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:14
msgid ""
"[`asm-code-width`](assembly-conventions.md#asm-code-width): `.code64`/`."
"code32` after the section definition for single-mode sections."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:15
msgid ""
"[`asm-function-attributes`](assembly-conventions.md#asm-function-"
"attributes): Place `.global`/`.balign`/`.type` directly before the function "
"label; prefer `.global`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:16
msgid ""
"[`asm-type-and-size`](assembly-conventions.md#asm-type-and-size): Give Rust-"
"callable functions `.type @function` and `.size` (not boot/trap trampolines)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:17
msgid ""
"[`asm-label-prefixes`](assembly-conventions.md#asm-label-prefixes): Prefix "
"`global_asm!` labels (e.g. `bsp_`) to avoid clashes in the crate namespace."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:18
msgid ""
"[`asm-prefer-balign`](assembly-conventions.md#asm-prefer-balign): Use `."
"balign` (byte-count) over arch-dependent `.align`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:20
msgid "**[CPU Architecture-Specific](cpu-architecture-specific/)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:21
msgid "[x86-64](cpu-architecture-specific/x86-64.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-hardware/index.md:22
msgid ""
"[`16b-align-rsp-before-call`](cpu-architecture-specific/x86-64.md#16b-align-"
"rsp-before-call): Ensure 16-byte alignment before making a function call."
msgstr ""
